Cost-Effectiveness of Immediate Magnetic Resonance Imaging In the Management of 
Patients With Suspected Scaphoid Fracture: Results From a Randomized Clinical 
Trial.

Rua T(1), Gidwani S(2), Malhotra B(3), Vijayanathan S(3), Hunter L(4), Peacock 
J(5), Turville J(3), Razavi R(6), Goh V(7), McCrone P(8), Shearer J(8).

Author information:
(1)King's Health Economics, King's College London, London, England, UK; 
Department of Radiology, Guy's and St Thomas' NHS Foundation Trust, London, 
England, UK. Electronic address: tiago.rua@kcl.ac.uk.
